      "Hi,\r\n\r\nYou can do this with \"rethinkdb admin set replicas DB.TABLE 2 --join\r\nhost:port\".  You can read more about that by running \"rethinkdb admin help\r\nset\".  (Unfortunately you can't do this from the client drivers right now;\r\nyou have to shell out to `rethinkdb admin`.)\r\n\r\n\r\nOn Thu, Aug 7, 2014 at 3:58 AM, aktarali <notifications@github.com> wrote:\r\n\r\n> Hi;\r\n>\r\n> I have 1 DB, and 2 servers in the cluster. 1 in each AZ. I want to\r\n> programmatically set all tables settings for replication to 2.\r\n> Replication settings\r\n> 2 replicas 1 write acks.\r\n>\r\n> How do I do that for all the tables. I do not want to modify the\r\n> multi-dc-options. Just have 1 primary and 1 secondary for every table.\r\n>\r\n> Please advise.\r\n>\r\n> Thanks\r\n> Ali.\r\n>\r\n> \8212\r\n> Reply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\r\n> <https://github.com/rethinkdb/rethinkdb/issues/1792#issuecomment-51457512>\r\n> .\r\n>"
